{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":635,"text":"I've been a journalist now since I was about 17,"},{"time":3256,"text":"and it's an interesting industry to be in at the moment,"},{"time":6816,"text":"because as you all know, there's a huge amount of upheaval"},{"time":9152,"text":"going on in media, and most of you probably know this"},{"time":11632,"text":"from the business angle, which is that the business model"},{"time":14855,"text":"is pretty screwed, and as my grandfather would say,"},{"time":17798,"text":"the profits have all been gobbled up by Google."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20512,"text":"So it's a really interesting time to be a journalist,"},{"time":22856,"text":"but the upheaval that I'm interested in is not on the output side."},{"time":25940,"text":"It's on the input side. It's concern with"},{"time":29035,"text":"how we get information and how we gather the news."},{"time":31533,"text":"And that's changed, because we've had a huge shift"},{"time":34604,"text":"in the balance of power from"},{"time":36842,"text":"the news organizations to the audience."},{"time":38859,"text":"And the audience for such a long time was in a position"},{"time":41074,"text":"where they didn't have any way of affecting news"},{"time":43764,"text":"or making any change. They couldn't really connect."},{"time":46031,"text":"And that's changed irrevocably."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47507,"text":"My first connection with the news media was"},{"time":50396,"text":"in 1984, the BBC had a one-day strike."},{"time":54207,"text":"I wasn't happy. I was angry. I couldn't see my cartoons."},{"time":57495,"text":"So I wrote a letter."},{"time":60042,"text":"And it's a very effective way of ending your hate mail:"},{"time":62891,"text":"\"Love Markham, Aged 4.\" Still works."},{"time":65978,"text":"I'm not sure if I had any impact on the one-day strike,"},{"time":68989,"text":"but what I do know is that it took them three weeks to get back to me."},{"time":71671,"text":"And that was the round journey. It took that long for anyone"},{"time":73831,"text":"to have any impact and get some feedback."},{"time":76024,"text":"And that's changed now because, as journalists,"},{"time":78506,"text":"we interact in real time. We're not in a position"},{"time":81672,"text":"where the audience is reacting to news."},{"time":84006,"text":"We're reacting to the audience, and we're actually relying on them."},{"time":87763,"text":"They're helping us find the news. They're helping us"},{"time":90149,"text":"figure out what is the best angle to take and what is the stuff that they want to hear."},{"time":94919,"text":"So it's a real-time thing. It's much quicker. It's happening"},{"time":98823,"text":"on a constant basis, and the journalist is always playing catch up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104740,"text":"To give an example of how we rely on the audience,"},{"time":107373,"text":"on the 5th of September in Costa Rica, an earthquake hit."},{"time":111910,"text":"It was a 7.6 magnitude. It was fairly big."},{"time":114236,"text":"And 60 seconds is the amount of time it took"},{"time":117116,"text":"for it to travel 250 kilometers to Managua."},{"time":119681,"text":"So the ground shook in Managua 60 seconds after it hit the epicenter."},{"time":123826,"text":"Thirty seconds later, the first message went onto Twitter,"},{"time":126482,"text":"and this was someone saying \"temblor,\" which means earthquake."},{"time":129343,"text":"So 60 seconds was how long it took"},{"time":131680,"text":"for the physical earthquake to travel."},{"time":133586,"text":"Thirty seconds later news of that earthquake had traveled"},{"time":136146,"text":"all around the world, instantly. Everyone in the world,"},{"time":139120,"text":"hypothetically, had the potential to know that an earthquake"},{"time":142317,"text":"was happening in Managua."},{"time":144731,"text":"And that happened because this one person had"},{"time":147082,"text":"a documentary instinct, which was to post a status update,"},{"time":151031,"text":"which is what we all do now, so if something happens,"},{"time":153563,"text":"we put our status update, or we post a photo,"},{"time":155645,"text":"we post a video, and it all goes up into the cloud in a constant stream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159423,"text":"And what that means is just constant,"},{"time":162184,"text":"huge volumes of data going up."},{"time":164590,"text":"It's actually staggering. When you look at the numbers,"},{"time":166871,"text":"every minute there are 72 more hours"},{"time":169862,"text":"of video on YouTube."},{"time":171244,"text":"So that's, every second, more than an hour of video gets uploaded."},{"time":174526,"text":"And in photos, Instagram, 58 photos are uploaded to Instagram a second."},{"time":178782,"text":"More than three and a half thousand photos go up onto Facebook."},{"time":182538,"text":"So by the time I'm finished talking here, there'll be 864"},{"time":186246,"text":"more hours of video on Youtube than there were when I started,"},{"time":189864,"text":"and two and a half million more photos on Facebook and Instagram than when I started."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193727,"text":"So it's an interesting position to be in as a journalist,"},{"time":197659,"text":"because we should have access to everything."},{"time":200075,"text":"Any event that happens anywhere in the world, I should be able to know about it"},{"time":202973,"text":"pretty much instantaneously, as it happens, for free."},{"time":206904,"text":"And that goes for every single person in this room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210069,"text":"The only problem is, when you have that much information,"},{"time":212679,"text":"you have to find the good stuff, and that can be"},{"time":214966,"text":"incredibly difficult when you're dealing with those volumes."},{"time":216954,"text":"And nowhere was this brought home more than during"},{"time":219273,"text":"Hurricane Sandy. So what you had in Hurricane Sandy was"},{"time":222177,"text":"a superstorm, the likes of which we hadn't seen for a long time,"},{"time":225204,"text":"hitting the iPhone capital of the universe -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":228347,"text":"and you got volumes of media like we'd never seen before."},{"time":232562,"text":"And that meant that journalists had to deal with fakes,"},{"time":235306,"text":"so we had to deal with old photos that were being reposted."},{"time":238222,"text":"We had to deal with composite images"},{"time":240470,"text":"that were merging photos from previous storms."},{"time":243653,"text":"We had to deal with images from films like \"The Day After Tomorrow.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":248887,"text":"And we had to deal with images that were so realistic"},{"time":251721,"text":"it was nearly difficult to tell if they were real at all."},{"time":254091,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":258404,"text":"But joking aside, there were images like this one from Instagram"},{"time":262128,"text":"which was subjected to a grilling by journalists."},{"time":264404,"text":"They weren't really sure. It was filtered in Instagram."},{"time":266637,"text":"The lighting was questioned. Everything was questioned about it."},{"time":269160,"text":"And it turned out to be true. It was from Avenue C"},{"time":271453,"text":"in downtown Manhattan, which was flooded."},{"time":273613,"text":"And the reason that they could tell that it was real"},{"time":275713,"text":"was because they could get to the source, and in this case,"},{"time":277802,"text":"these guys were New York food bloggers."},{"time":279909,"text":"They were well respected. They were known."},{"time":281939,"text":"So this one wasn't a debunk, it was actually something that they could prove."},{"time":285031,"text":"And that was the job of the journalist. It was filtering all this stuff."},{"time":287949,"text":"And you were, instead of going and finding the information"},{"time":290660,"text":"and bringing it back to the reader, you were holding back"},{"time":293227,"text":"the stuff that was potentially damaging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295287,"text":"And finding the source becomes more and more important --"},{"time":298245,"text":"finding the good source -- and Twitter is where most journalists now go."},{"time":301979,"text":"It's like the de facto real-time newswire,"},{"time":305132,"text":"if you know how to use it, because there is so much on Twitter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308099,"text":"And a good example of how useful it can be"},{"time":310484,"text":"but also how difficult was the Egyptian revolution in 2011."},{"time":314017,"text":"As a non-Arabic speaker, as someone who was looking"},{"time":316663,"text":"from the outside, from Dublin,"},{"time":318964,"text":"Twitter lists, and lists of good sources,"},{"time":320756,"text":"people we could establish were credible, were really important."},{"time":324378,"text":"And how do you build a list like that from scratch?"},{"time":326887,"text":"Well, it can be quite difficult, but you have to know what to look for."},{"time":329317,"text":"This visualization was done by an Italian academic."},{"time":332175,"text":"He's called Andr√© Pannison, and he basically"},{"time":335569,"text":"took the Twitter conversation in Tahrir Square"},{"time":337744,"text":"on the day that Hosni Mubarak would eventually resign,"},{"time":341198,"text":"and the dots you can see are retweets, so when someone"},{"time":343830,"text":"retweets a message, a connection is made between two dots,"},{"time":346609,"text":"and the more times that message is retweeted by other people,"},{"time":349219,"text":"the more you get to see these nodes, these connections being made."},{"time":352425,"text":"And it's an amazing way of visualizing the conversation,"},{"time":354347,"text":"but what you get is hints at who is more interesting"},{"time":357058,"text":"and who is worth investigating."},{"time":359739,"text":"And as the conversation grew and grew, it became"},{"time":362618,"text":"more and more lively, and eventually you were left"},{"time":364902,"text":"with this huge, big, rhythmic pointer of this conversation."},{"time":369683,"text":"You could find the nodes, though, and then you went,"},{"time":371492,"text":"and you go, \"Right, I've got to investigate these people."},{"time":373786,"text":"These are the ones that are obviously making sense."},{"time":375500,"text":"Let's see who they are.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":377809,"text":"Now in the deluge of information, this is where"},{"time":380499,"text":"the real-time web gets really interesting for a journalist like myself,"},{"time":383706,"text":"because we have more tools than ever"},{"time":385680,"text":"to do that kind of investigation."},{"time":388437,"text":"And when you start digging into the sources, you can go"},{"time":391446,"text":"further and further than you ever could before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393745,"text":"Sometimes you come across a piece of content that"},{"time":397097,"text":"is so compelling, you want to use it, you're dying to use it,"},{"time":400557,"text":"but you're not 100 percent sure if you can because"},{"time":403232,"text":"you don't know if the source is credible."},{"time":404439,"text":"You don't know if it's a scrape. You don't know if it's a re-upload."},{"time":406621,"text":"And you have to do that investigative work."},{"time":408330,"text":"And this video, which I'm going to let run through,"},{"time":410674,"text":"was one we discovered a couple of weeks ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413663,"text":"Video: Getting real windy in just a second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415862,"text":"(Rain and wind sounds)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":420750,"text":"(Explosion) Oh, shit!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":423917,"text":"Markham Nolan: Okay, so now if you're a news producer, this is something"},{"time":426854,"text":"you'd love to run with, because obviously, this is gold."},{"time":429406,"text":"You know? This is a fantastic reaction from someone,"},{"time":431669,"text":"very genuine video that they've shot in their back garden."},{"time":434239,"text":"But how do you find if this person, if it's true, if it's faked,"},{"time":437733,"text":"or if it's something that's old and that's been reposted?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":440391,"text":"So we set about going to work on this video, and"},{"time":442617,"text":"the only thing that we had to go on was the username on the YouTube account."},{"time":445477,"text":"There was only one video posted to that account,"},{"time":447828,"text":"and the username was Rita Krill."},{"time":449316,"text":"And we didn't know if Rita existed or if it was a fake name."},{"time":452608,"text":"But we started looking, and we used free Internet tools to do so."},{"time":455521,"text":"The first one was called Spokeo, which allowed us to look for Rita Krills."},{"time":458829,"text":"So we looked all over the U.S. We found them in New York,"},{"time":461211,"text":"we found them in Pennsylvania, Nevada and Florida."},{"time":463973,"text":"So we went and we looked for a second free Internet tool"},{"time":466622,"text":"called Wolfram Alpha, and we checked the weather reports"},{"time":469089,"text":"for the day in which this video had been uploaded,"},{"time":471586,"text":"and when we went through all those various cities,"},{"time":473469,"text":"we found that in Florida, there were thunderstorms and rain on the day."},{"time":476965,"text":"So we went to the white pages, and we found,"},{"time":479610,"text":"we looked through the Rita Krills in the phonebook,"},{"time":482534,"text":"and we looked through a couple of different addresses,"},{"time":484106,"text":"and that took us to Google Maps, where we found a house."},{"time":487422,"text":"And we found a house with a swimming pool that looked"},{"time":489337,"text":"remarkably like Rita's. So we went back to the video,"},{"time":492255,"text":"and we had to look for clues that we could cross-reference."},{"time":495226,"text":"So if you look in the video, there's the big umbrella,"},{"time":498441,"text":"there's a white lilo in the pool,"},{"time":500286,"text":"there are some unusually rounded edges in the swimming pool,"},{"time":502726,"text":"and there's two trees in the background."},{"time":504780,"text":"And we went back to Google Maps, and we looked a little bit closer,"},{"time":507207,"text":"and sure enough, there's the white lilo,"},{"time":509878,"text":"there are the two trees,"},{"time":512872,"text":"there's the umbrella. It's actually folded in this photo."},{"time":514858,"text":"Little bit of trickery. And there are the rounded edges on the swimming pool."},{"time":518636,"text":"So we were able to call Rita, clear the video,"},{"time":521786,"text":"make sure that it had been shot, and then our clients"},{"time":523872,"text":"were delighted because they were able to run it without being worried."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527066,"text":"Sometimes the search for truth, though,"},{"time":528841,"text":"is a little bit less flippant, and it has much greater consequences."},{"time":533250,"text":"Syria has been really interesting for us, because obviously"},{"time":536233,"text":"a lot of the time you're trying to debunk stuff that can be"},{"time":538914,"text":"potentially war crime evidence, so this is where YouTube"},{"time":542713,"text":"actually becomes the most important repository"},{"time":545070,"text":"of information about what's going on in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549220,"text":"So this video, I'm not going to show you the whole thing,"},{"time":551974,"text":"because it's quite gruesome, but you'll hear some of the sounds."},{"time":554695,"text":"This is from Hama."},{"time":557023,"text":"Video: (Shouting)"},{"time":559993,"text":"And what this video shows, when you watch the whole thing through,"},{"time":563897,"text":"is bloody bodies being taken out of a pickup truck"},{"time":566658,"text":"and thrown off a bridge."},{"time":569263,"text":"The allegations were that these guys were Muslim Brotherhood"},{"time":572044,"text":"and they were throwing Syrian Army officers' bodies"},{"time":574919,"text":"off the bridge, and they were cursing and using blasphemous language,"},{"time":577853,"text":"and there were lots of counterclaims about who they were,"},{"time":580235,"text":"and whether or not they were what the video said it was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582477,"text":"So we talked to some sources in Hama who we had been"},{"time":585743,"text":"back and forth with on Twitter, and we asked them about this,"},{"time":588076,"text":"and the bridge was interesting to us because it was something we could identify."},{"time":591890,"text":"Three different sources said three different things about the bridge."},{"time":594804,"text":"They said, one, the bridge doesn't exist."},{"time":597066,"text":"Another one said the bridge does exist, but it's not in Hama. It's somewhere else."},{"time":600590,"text":"And the third one said, \"I think the bridge does exist,"},{"time":603152,"text":"but the dam upstream of the bridge was closed,"},{"time":606516,"text":"so the river should actually have been dry, so this doesn't make sense.\""},{"time":609913,"text":"So that was the only one that gave us a clue."},{"time":612525,"text":"We looked through the video for other clues."},{"time":613750,"text":"We saw the distinctive railings, which we could use."},{"time":616839,"text":"We looked at the curbs. The curbs were throwing shadows south,"},{"time":620583,"text":"so we could tell the bridge was running east-west across the river."},{"time":622900,"text":"It had black-and-white curbs."},{"time":624856,"text":"As we looked at the river itself, you could see there's"},{"time":626842,"text":"a concrete stone on the west side. There's a cloud of blood."},{"time":629796,"text":"That's blood in the river. So the river is flowing"},{"time":631530,"text":"south to north. That's what that tells me."},{"time":633227,"text":"And also, as you look away from the bridge,"},{"time":635576,"text":"there's a divot on the left-hand side of the bank,"},{"time":637225,"text":"and the river narrows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639655,"text":"So onto Google Maps we go, and we start"},{"time":642234,"text":"looking through literally every single bridge."},{"time":644292,"text":"We go to the dam that we talked about, we start just"},{"time":647772,"text":"literally going through every time that road crosses the river,"},{"time":651382,"text":"crossing off the bridges that don't match."},{"time":653120,"text":"We're looking for one that crosses east-west."},{"time":654883,"text":"And we get to Hama. We get all the way from the dam"},{"time":656835,"text":"to Hama and there's no bridge."},{"time":658838,"text":"So we go a bit further. We switch to the satellite view,"},{"time":661322,"text":"and we find another bridge, and everything starts to line up."},{"time":664242,"text":"The bridge looks like it's crossing the river east to west."},{"time":667280,"text":"So this could be our bridge. And we zoom right in."},{"time":670441,"text":"We start to see that it's got a median, so it's a two-lane bridge."},{"time":673343,"text":"And it's got the black-and-white curbs that we saw in the video,"},{"time":676989,"text":"and as we click through it, you can see someone's"},{"time":679301,"text":"uploaded photos to go with the map, which is very handy,"},{"time":682255,"text":"so we click into the photos. And the photos start showing us"},{"time":684942,"text":"more detail that we can cross-reference with the video."},{"time":687564,"text":"The first thing that we see is we see black-and-white curbing,"},{"time":691287,"text":"which is handy because we've seen that before."},{"time":693392,"text":"We see the distinctive railing that we saw the guys"},{"time":696891,"text":"throwing the bodies over."},{"time":699242,"text":"And we keep going through it until we're certain that this is our bridge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701897,"text":"So what does that tell me? I've got to go back now"},{"time":703421,"text":"to my three sources and look at what they told me:"},{"time":705734,"text":"the one who said the bridge didn't exist,"},{"time":707459,"text":"the one who said the bridge wasn't in Hama,"},{"time":709318,"text":"and the one guy who said, \"Yes, the bridge does exist, but I'm not sure about the water levels.\""},{"time":713271,"text":"Number three is looking like the most truthful all of a sudden,"},{"time":716602,"text":"and we've been able to find that out using some free Internet tools"},{"time":719583,"text":"sitting in a cubicle in an office in Dublin"},{"time":722103,"text":"in the space of 20 minutes."},{"time":723590,"text":"And that's part of the joy of this. Although the web"},{"time":726029,"text":"is running like a torrent, there's so much information there"},{"time":729294,"text":"that it's incredibly hard to sift and getting harder every day,"},{"time":732481,"text":"if you use them intelligently, you can find out incredible information."},{"time":735808,"text":"Given a couple of clues, I could probably find out"},{"time":738203,"text":"a lot of things about most of you in the audience that you might not like me finding out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741737,"text":"But what it tells me is that, at a time when"},{"time":744742,"text":"there's more -- there's a greater abundance of information than there ever has been,"},{"time":748771,"text":"it's harder to filter, we have greater tools."},{"time":751404,"text":"We have free Internet tools that allow us,"},{"time":753267,"text":"help us do this kind of investigation."},{"time":755493,"text":"We have algorithms that are smarter than ever before,"},{"time":757316,"text":"and computers that are quicker than ever before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759737,"text":"But here's the thing. Algorithms are rules. They're binary."},{"time":763164,"text":"They're yes or no, they're black or white."},{"time":764949,"text":"Truth is never binary. Truth is a value."},{"time":768503,"text":"Truth is emotional, it's fluid, and above all, it's human."},{"time":773167,"text":"No matter how quick we get with computers, no matter"},{"time":775274,"text":"how much information we have, you'll never be able"},{"time":777658,"text":"to remove the human from the truth-seeking exercise,"},{"time":780654,"text":"because in the end, it is a uniquely human trait."},{"time":784312,"text":"Thanks very much. (Applause)"}]}]}